topic.body:
UFS Explorer Professional Recovery v5.18.4


All-in-one data recovery tool
Fast and high-quality pre-recovery data analysis and data recovery using single utility.

Fast test of data consistency
Using context dependent storage navigation, files and folders contents identification, fragmentation details etc.

Recovery from replaced file systems
Accurate detection of current and previous file systems after format and targeting recovery process at certain file system state.

RAID Builder and Analyzer
Single utility to analyse and virtually reconstruct complex RAID storages.

Disk-on-Disk recovery
Open disk image files and virtual disks stored on virtual storages of UFS Explorer and recover data at once without recovery of temporary disk image file.

Usability extensions
Extend software tool set with optional external modules (plugins).


Specifications

Supported host operating systems:

    Microsoft Windows ®: starting with Windows ® XP with Service Pack 3 and later;
    Apple Mac OS X: all starting with version 10.7 and above;
    Linux: Debian Linux 6.0 (or compatible) and above. 

Supported host computer architectures:

    Intel Architecture, 32-bit (IA-32, x86) - for all operating systems;
    AMD64 (x86-64) - for all operating systems. 

Supported file systems for recovery:

    NTFS: full support (access and advanced recovery);
    Windows Server ReFS: full support (access and advanced recovery);
    Sun ZFS: full support (access and advanced recovery) for simple ZPOOL, no support for RAID-Z;
    FAT/FAT32: full support (access and advanced recovery);
    ExFAT: full support (access and advanced recovery);
    SGI XFS: full support (access and advanced recovery);
    Apple HFS+: full support (access and advanced recovery*);
    JFS (IBM JFS2): full support (access and advanced recovery);
    Ext2-Ext4: full support (access and advanced recovery*);
    ReiserFS: full support (access and advanced recovery);
    Btrfs: data access and failed RAID recovery only;
    UFS/UFS2: access and damaged file system recovery** in both little-endian and big-endian variations;
    Custom Adaptec UFS: access and damaged file system recovery**;
    HFS: legacy Apple file system supported in data access mode only (copies files and folders from HFS file system);
    Novell NWFS: legacy Novell file system supported in data access and data analysis mode only;
    Novell NSS: modern Novell Storage Services file system supported in data access mode only;
    VMware VMFS: data access and basic recovery (software can copy files and virtual disks from VMFS file system and perform basic scan for lost and deleted VMDK files). 

* - the rate of deleted files recovery can be low due to the file system design
** - deleted files may be unrecoverable due to the file system design


Full feature list here: 
